<section class="py-24 sm:py-32 px-5 sm:px-8 section-divide">
  <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto">
    <p class="font-mono text-xs text-text-muted uppercase tracking-widest mb-4 reveal">Design philosophy</p>
    <h2 class="font-display text-3xl sm:text-4xl lg:text-5xl italic leading-tight mb-16 reveal stagger-1">
      Built for how supervision actually works.
    </h2>

    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-x-12 gap-y-14">
      <!-- Principle 1 -->
      <div class="reveal stagger-2">
        <div class="flex items-baseline gap-3 mb-3">
          <span class="font-mono text-xs text-accent">01</span>
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold">Glanceable over interactive</h3>
        </div>
        <p class="text-text-muted text-sm leading-relaxed pl-8">
          Open the app, see that three agents are running and one needs input, tap in, type "yes", close the app. Ten seconds. The interface is built for that rhythm.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Principle 2 -->
      <div class="reveal stagger-3">
        <div class="flex items-baseline gap-3 mb-3">
          <span class="font-mono text-xs text-accent">02</span>
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold">Don't recreate the laptop</h3>
        </div>
        <p class="text-text-muted text-sm leading-relaxed pl-8">
          Your phone is not where you write code. It's where you supervise code being written. No code editor. Just a terminal to read, a file browser to review, and an input bar for short instructions.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Principle 3 -->
      <div class="reveal stagger-4">
        <div class="flex items-baseline gap-3 mb-3">
          <span class="font-mono text-xs text-accent">03</span>
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold">Show me the work</h3>
        </div>
        <p class="text-text-muted text-sm leading-relaxed pl-8">
          The value of a session isn't the conversation. It's the changes in the working directory. Marmy renders the artifacts: syntax-highlighted code, formatted markdown, images, PDFs. That's supervising.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Principle 4 -->
      <div class="reveal stagger-5">
        <div class="flex items-baseline gap-3 mb-3">
          <span class="font-mono text-xs text-accent">04</span>
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold">Sessions are cheap</h3>
        </div>
        <p class="text-text-muted text-sm leading-relaxed pl-8">
          Something went sideways? Kill it, start fresh with better instructions. Two taps. Your code is in git. The session is just the conversation. Treat it that way.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
